<TITLE> Vessel sinks in Ctg, ship movement unaffected </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, May 7 (bdnews24.com)A cement clinker-laden lightering vessel anchored in the outer anchorage zone of Chittagong port sank on Thursday morning, an official said. Arif Ahmed, member, Chittagong Port Authority, told bdnews24.com, "Ship movement in the port, however, is not going to be affected by the accident." CPA radio control tower said while lightering vessel Titu-9 was loading itself with cement clinker from the Honduran flag carrier Morris Thursday morning, another large vessel Metro Glorobis-2 rammed into Titu-9, drowning it in 10-15 minutes. Titu-9 had 13 sailors on board, who managed to board another ship. Syed Farhaduddin, CPA secretary, told bdnews24.com, "The accident spot was marked with a buoy then and there so that other vessels could avoid the sunken boat." "For retrieving the vessel, its owner has been informed of the mishap." He said a committee will be formed to investigate the matter. On Apr 21, another clinker-laden vessel Seven Circle-25 capsized in the Chittagong port channel in the Karnaphuli estuary. bdnew
